The Aero Club of East Africa on Thursday evening hosted its members to an evening of networking to celebrate the achievements of Wilson Airport since its inception 89years ago.The evening also acted as a pre-gala event for the 90th anniversary celebrations expected to be held early next year.Among those present were Kenya Airways managing director Mbuvi Ngunze, Aero club chairman Simon Herd, Rolls-Royce vice president Kevin Evans and Astral Aviation chief commercial officer Charles Simiyu among many others.